{"title_page": "Ohio State University at Marion", "text_new": "{{cleanup university|date=January 2016}}\n{{More citations needed|date=January 2010}}\n{{Coord|40.58153|-83.089213|region:US_type:edu|display=title}}\n{{Infobox University\n|name            = The Ohio State University at Marion\n|image_name      = \n|image_upright   = 0.8\n|motto           = ''Disciplina in civitatem'' ([[Latin]])\n|mottoeng        = Education for Citizenship\n|established     = 1957\n|type            = [[Public university|Public]]\n|parent          = [[Ohio State University]]\n|endowment       =\n|staff           =\n|faculty         = 205\n|president       = [[Michael V. Drake]]\n|chancellor      = \n|vice_chancellor =\n|dean            = Gregory S. Rose\n|students        = 1,274<ref name=\"headcount\">As of fall 2019. {{cite web | title=15th Day Headcount, Fall Term 2019 | url=https://www.ohiohighered.org/sites/default/files/uploads/data/enrollment/Preliminary_hc_2019_101719.pdf | publisher=Ohio Department of Higher Education | access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n|undergrad       = 1,262<ref name=headcount/>\n|postgrad        = 12<ref name=headcount/>\n|doctoral        =\n|city            = [[Marion, Ohio|Marion]]\n|state           = [[Ohio]]\n|country         = United States\n|campus          = [[Suburban]]<br>187 [[acre]]s\n|free_label      = \n|free            = \n|colors          = Scarlet and Gray {{color box|#990000}}&nbsp;{{color box|#999999}}\n|mascot          = \n|nickname        = Scarlet Wave\n|affiliations    = [[Ohio Regional Campus Conference|ORCC]]\n|logo            = Ohio_State_University_at_Marion_Logo.png \n|logo_size       = 150px\n|website         = {{URL|http://osumarion.osu.edu}}\n}}\n\n'''The Ohio State University at Marion''' ('''OSU Marion''' or '''OSUM''') is a regional campus of [[Ohio State University|The Ohio State University]] located in [[Marion, Ohio]], United States. The campus was founded in 1957. Its {{convert|187|acre|km2|sing=on}} campus is located {{convert|45|mi|km}} north of [[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus]] and is shared with [[Marion Technical College]]. There are eight buildings on the campus.\n\nOhio State Marion has baccalaureate program accreditation with [[NCATE]]. The Marion campus practices [[open admissions]].<ref>{{cite web\n | url = http://osumarion.osu.edu/future-students/adult-students/requirements/ | title = Admission Requirements | publisher = The Ohio State University at Marion | access-date = 1 February 2018}}</ref> Its average class size is 19<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://osumarion.osu.edu/about/quick-facts.html|title=Quick Facts {{!}} The Ohio State University at Marion |website=osumarion.osu.edu|access-date=2017-01-23}}</ref>. An average age of students is 23.5. The Marion Campus Library of the OSU Marion Campus contains over 48,000 books, a large reference collection, and over 300 subscriptions. The library collection also includes print periodical indexes, microforms, maps, newspapers, pamphlet file, special collections in careers and children's literature, and the Warren G. Harding/Norman Thomas Research Collection.  It provides access to all the resources of The Ohio State University and Ohio Link.\n\nAbout 88% of students at the Marion campus are awarded federal or state financial aid. The student body is 53% female and 47% male. Students who start at Marion may finish their degrees at the [[Ohio State University|Columbus campus]] with one of Ohio State's 200+ [[Academic major|majors]]. The Academy Program at the campus provides the opportunity for qualified students to enroll in college while still in high school as part of Ohio's College Credit Plus program. The Alber Enterprise Center is a campus-based corporate education center that provides workforce training, organization development, and performance improvement techniques.\n\n==Academics==\n[[File:Maynard Hall.JPG|thumb|left|Maynard Hall]]\n[[File:Morrill Hall.JPG|thumb|left|Morrill Hall]]\nStudents may complete one-to-three years of Ohio State University\u2019s over 200 majors (available coursework varies by major) in Marion before making the transition to the Columbus campus to complete their degree.<ref>https://osumarion.osu.edu/academics/majors.html</ref>\n\n==Athletics==\nOn December 2, 2006, [[Lincoln University (Pennsylvania)|Lincoln University]] defeated Ohio State Marion in basketball with a final score of 201-78. This set new all-time [[NCAA Division III]] basketball records for points scored (201), points in a half (104), largest margin of victory (123), shots made (78), and shots taken (141).<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.espn.com/mens-college-basketball/news/story?id=2683783\n |title=Lincoln sets D-III record for points in game, half\n |last=Santoliquito\n |first=Joseph\n |date=3 December 2006\n |website=ESPN\n |publisher=\n |access-date=30 November 2017\n |quote= }}</ref>\n\nThe Marion campus does not currently offer varsity athletic teams. A club level soccer team is active on the campus.\n\n==Student life==\n\n===Student organizations===\nThere are over 30 student clubs on campus.<ref>{{cite web\n | url = http://osumarion.osu.edu/student-life/student-organizations.html | title = Student Organizations | publisher = The Ohio State University at Marion\n | access-date = 1 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Sport clubs and intramural sports===\nStudents at the Marion Campus can participate in several intramural sports such as basketball, softball, and volleyball.<ref>https://marioncampusrec.wordpress.com</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://osumarion.osu.edu Official website]\n\n{{Ohio State University|campus}}\n\n[[Category:Ohio State University campuses|Marion Campus, Ohio State University]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1957]]\n[[Category:Education in Marion County, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Marion, Ohio]]\n", "text_old": "{{cleanup university|date=January 2016}}\n{{More citations nee